name: Nobody Wants This
overview: An agnostic sex podcaster and a newly single rabbi fall in love, but can their relationship survive their wildly different lives and meddling families?
tagline: Will they. Won't they. Should they?

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Fresh off another unsuccessful date, Joanne sashays into a friend's party and meets Noah, an adorable rabbi who recently broke up with his girlfriend.

episodes.name: A Shiksa Walks Into a Temple
episodes.overview: Joanne and Noah get to know each other, but reality hits when she learns about his romantic history and he deals with an interrogation from his family.

episodes.name: Either Aura
episodes.overview: A podcast pile-on about her aura and an unanswered text make Joanne question if she's a good match for Noah, who faces a guilt trip after an accident.

episodes.name: Obliterated
episodes.overview: Joanne's last-minute dash to pick up a sex toy for a podcast episode makes for a memorable first date with Noah. Sasha helps Miriam with a boy problem.

episodes.name: My Friend Joanne
episodes.overview: Work obligations interfere with Noah and Joanne's plans to take their relationship to the next level, while Sasha and Morgan bond over family dynamics.

episodes.name: The Ick
episodes.overview: During an impromptu get-together with Joanne's family, Noah is determined to make a good impression — so determined that it's a major turnoff.

episodes.name: WAGS
episodes.overview: Meeting Joanne's friends? Easy enough for Noah. But winning over his pals means making nice with their wives and girlfriends, who are close to his ex.

episodes.name: Rebecca's Box
episodes.overview: Joanne's discovery of a small box in Noah's bedroom turns into something much bigger as she fights the urge to snoop, and he receives big news at work.

episodes.name: My Girl Bina
episodes.overview: Power games and a custom-made charcuterie board complicate Joanne's official introduction to Noah's parents. Morgan asks Sasha for a favor.

episodes.name: Bat Mitzvah Crashers
episodes.overview: Miriam's Big Apple-themed bat mitzvah sets the scene for even greater life changes when Noah and Joanne confront questions about their future.
